I'm so sorry to hear that your sister is unwell. Please call emergency services or try to reach your parents first. If they aren't available, you can:
1. Give her a warm cloth compress to help with the fever (avoid direct sunlight);
2. Offer small sips of water or electrolyte solutions;
3. Try to keep her calm with gentle breathing exercises (you can do this together);
4. Use a clean towel to apply cool compresses alternated with warm compresses for better fever reduction;

For future emergencies, you can prepare these supplies in advance: thermometer, precision digital thermometer, soaked cotton balls for oral temperature measurement, quick-cooling medicine drinks, small plastic containers for cold compresses, and enclosures for warm water compresses. This preparedness plan can help protect your sister's health even when parents aren't around.
